    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hmm, just saw `pd.Categorical.from_codes` in the docs. So it'd be `pd.Categorical.from_codes(new_codes, s.cat.categories)`, which isn't terrible to type. Just wasn't the first place I looked. I'll close this unless anyone else thinks adding essentially that method to the `.cat` accessor, just with `categories` already assigned, would be useful.\n\nso\n\n``` python\n>>> s.cat.categorize(new_codes)\n# rather than\n>>> pd.Categorical.from_codes(new_codes, s.cat.categories)\n```\n"
